    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "Accuracy counts correct labels. Confidence is a separate claim \u2014 how certain the model is, not just whether it got the label right.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "scene_class": "B04_AccuracyVsConf",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.76,
      "audio_file": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-calibration-curve/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8.5,
      "narration_text": "When the model assigns ninety-nine percent to a case, it is making a promise: ninety-nine of every hundred similar cases should be positive.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "trace"
      },
      "scene_class": "B05_NinetyNinePromise",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.39,
      "audio_file": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-calibration-curve/clips/B05.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B05.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 6.0,
      "narration_text": "Run the model on a held-out set. Collect every case where it reported ninety-nine percent confidence. Then check what actually happened.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "STILL",
        "source": "ai",
        "motion": "kenburns",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
          "version": "1",
          "props": {
            "headline": "Run the model on a held-out set. Collect every case where\u2026",
            "eyebrow": "THE MECHANISM",
            "topic": "COMPUTATIONAL SKEPTICISM"
          },
          "rendered": {
            "out": "media/B06.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "image_description": "A stream of prediction outputs on a screen, each labeled with a high confidence percentage, against a blurred data-center background",
      "chosen_media": null,
      "actual_duration_s": 8.07,
      "audio_file": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-calibration-curve/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.5,
      "narration_text": "There is a diagnostic for this. Stated confidence on one axis, actual frequency of positives on the other. A perfectly calibrated model traces the diagonal.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "scene_class": "B07_BlankDiagram",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.33,
      "audio_file": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-calibration-curve/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "Sort every prediction into a confidence bin. One bin for the low-confidence calls, one for the medium, one for the high. Each bin collects its cases.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "scene_class": "B08_PredictionsAccum",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.38,
      "audio_file": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-calibration-curve/clips/B08.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B08.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8.0,
      "narration_text": "If the model says seventy percent confident on a thousand cases, you want roughly seven hundred of those cases to turn out positive.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "DOCUMENT",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "highlight"
      },
      "scene_class": "B09_CalibContract",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.76,
      "audio_file": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-calibration-curve/clips/B09.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B09.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.5,
      "narration_text": "Count positives in each bin. Low-confidence bins track the claim. High-confidence bins fall short \u2014 outcomes arrive well below the stated number.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "scene_class": "B10_OutcomesAccum",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.43,
      "audio_file": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-calibration-curve/clips/B10.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B10.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8.5,
      "narration_text": "Connect those frequencies. The curve tracks the diagonal through the middle \u2014 then peels away at the top, where the model overclaims.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "scene_class": "B11_CalibCurve",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.07,
      "audio_file": "../vox-calibration-curve/mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "locked": true,
